      "writtenOn": "2026-05-06T00:51:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Due to the linename of Leak GPIO pins (https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/88602/3), we are not able to use $address variable to replace \"B0\" \u0026 \"B1\".\n\n- HPM0\n - \"B0_vLeakDetect1Status0-I\"\n - \"B0_vLeakDetect1Status1-I\"\n\n- HPM1\n - \"B1_vLeakDetect1Status0-I\"\n - \"B1_vLeakDetect1Status1-I\"\n\n\nIt seems that a space is needed after the formula, otherwise the string will be incorrect.\n\nFor example: (address \u003d 80)\n\"B$address - 80_vLeakDetect1Status0-I\"  --\u003e \"B0\"\n\"B$address - 80 _vLeakDetect1Status0-I\"  --\u003e \"B0 _vLeakDetect1Status0-I\"",
      "parentUuid": "7ab30f47_2167b8b0",
